---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Listening Device: Clarive"
  description="Read the Privacy Policy for Listening Device: Clarive. Learn how Harshva Technology collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
  path="/privacy-policy"
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal px-safe">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>Harshva Technology Private Limited ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency in how your personal data is collected, used, and safeguarded. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices across all digital touchpoints including our website, mobile applications, and any related services.</p>

    <p>By accessing or using our services, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please discontinue use of our services.</p>

    <p>This policy applies to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Our website: https://harshvatechnologies.com</li>
      <li>All mobile applications published under our developer account</li>
      <li>Any associated tools, features, or customer support services</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect information in a way that ensures functionality, performance, and continuous improvement of our services while maintaining a minimal data collection approach.</p>

    <h3>a) Information You Provide</h3>
    <p>When you interact with us directly, we may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide. This typically occurs when you contact support, submit feedback, or engage with our services. This may include your name, email address, contact details, and any messages, feedback, or queries.</p>

    <h3>b) Automatically Collected Information</h3>
    <p>When you use our website or applications, certain technical and usage-related information is collected automatically. This may include device type and operating system, IP address and general (non-precise) location, app version and interaction data, session duration, and crash logs or diagnostics. This data is generally aggregated and non-identifiable.</p>

    <h3>c) Permissions &amp; Media Access</h3>
    <p>Some of our applications may request access to device features such as the microphone strictly to enable core functionality — for example, capturing ambient sound for amplification and live captions. We do not access, store, or share your personal files unnecessarily, and audio processing happens locally on your device.</p>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the collected information to provide, operate, and maintain our services; improve functionality, speed, and user experience; respond to support inquiries; send important service-related notifications; analyze trends and optimize features; and detect, prevent, and address fraud or security issues.</p>

    <h2>3. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to store preferences, improve performance, and analyze traffic and engagement. You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>To operate efficiently, we may integrate trusted third-party services that support analytics, hosting, and app functionality — such as Apple's App Store for distribution, analytics tools, and cloud infrastructure providers. These third parties may process limited data under their own privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data. We may share data with service providers for analytics, hosting, or infrastructure; to comply with legal requirements or government requests; to protect our rights or prevent fraud; or during business transfers such as mergers or acquisitions.</p>

    <h2>6. Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
    <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data, including encryption where applicable, secure infrastructure, restricted access to sensitive information, and regular monitoring. While we strive to protect your data, no system is completely secure.</p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to provide and maintain services, comply with legal obligations, and resolve disputes. Once no longer required, it is securely deleted or anonymized.</p>

    <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to access your personal data, correct inaccurate information, request deletion, restrict or object to processing, and request a copy of your data (portability).</p>

    <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>Your information may be processed and stored in countries outside your own, which may have different data protection laws. By using our services, you consent to such transfers, provided reasonable safeguards are in place.</p>

    <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our services are not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If such data is identified, it will be deleted promptly.</p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in technology, legal requirements, or business practices. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.</p>

    <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@harshvatechnologies.com">support@harshvatechnologies.com</a>.</p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
